snippet.textDisplay:
Very nice....I like it ......
 But  I would like to say something about lyrics:

He said"Rah ma tul lil aa la meen" but acutally it is "Rah ma tal lil aa la meen"
There is two zabar instead of two paish..................
Because, according to Arabic Grammar it is ''Morakab e Izafi'', it has two parts of this compound word. And at the end of first part should be two zabar. Otherwise meaning will be changed.
You can also see this word in the Quran. This is in the Para 17 Surah Anbiaya Ayah No.107

So, be careful next time while pronouncing this word.
